\begin_layout Standard
Dirac matrix:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
D_{i,j}=\left(\frac{1}{2k}+i\mu\gamma_{5}\right)\delta_{i,j}-\frac{1}{2}\sum_{\mu}\left[\left(1+\gamma_{\mu}\right)U_{i,\mu}\delta_{i+\hat{\mu},j}+\left(1-\gamma_{\mu}\right)U_{i-\hat{\mu},\mu}^{\dagger}\delta_{i-\hat{\mu},j}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
that, separated in parity component is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
D=\left(\begin{array}{cc}
D_{ee} & D_{eo}\\
D_{oe} & D_{oo}
\end{array}\right)
\]

\end_inset

where in particular: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
D_{ee/oo}=\left(\frac{1}{2k}+i\gamma_{5}\mu\right)\delta_{ee/oo}
\]

\end_inset

We want to solve 
\begin_inset Formula $D\psi=\eta$
\end_inset

, which writing separate equations means:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
D_{ee}\psi_{e}+D_{eo}\psi_{o}=\eta_{e}\\
D_{oe}\psi_{e}+D_{oo}\psi_{o}=\eta_{o}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

We can solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{e}$
\end_inset

 from the first and substitute in the second:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{cases}
\psi_{e}=D_{ee}^{-1}\left(\eta_{e}-D_{eo}\psi_{o}\right)\\
D_{oe}D_{ee}^{-1}\left(\eta_{e}-D_{eo}\psi_{o}\right)+D_{oo}\psi_{o}=\eta_{o}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let's focus on the second.
 Muliplying the sink of both sides by 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma_{5}$
\end_inset

 (which will help when taking dagger) we get:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
K_{oo}\psi_{o}=\gamma_{5}\eta_{o}-\gamma_{5}D_{oe}D_{ee}^{-1}\eta_{e}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
K_{oo}\equiv\gamma_{5}\left(D_{oo}-D_{oe}D_{ee}^{-1}D_{eo}\right).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Reassuming, you can solve the problem in this way:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Define the spinor:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\begin{array}{c}
\chi_{e}\\
\chi_{o}
\end{array}\right)\equiv\left(\begin{array}{c}
D_{ee}^{-1}\eta_{e}\\
K_{oo}^{\dagger}\left(\gamma_{5}\eta_{o}-\gamma_{5}D_{oe}\chi_{e}\right)
\end{array}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Solve the problem:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
K_{oo}K_{oo}^{\dagger}\psi_{o}=\chi_{o}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Reconstruct: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\psi_{e}=D_{ee}^{-1}\left(\eta_{e}-D_{eo}\psi_{o}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to achieve better memory access is important that spinors and links
 are ordered as they are needed.
\end_layout

